For the sauce, place the blueberries and white wine into the bowl of a food processor  and blend the ingredients until smooth.For the tuna, place the tuna, sesame seeds and egg yolk into a clean bowl.  Season the ingredients with salt and freshly ground black pepper and mix well.Heat the olive oil in a frying pan and cook the tuna for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until cooked through.To serve, place the broccoli and sweet potato onto a clean plate.  Place the tuna on top of the broccoli and sweet potato and pour the sauce over the top.